com.singularity.ee.connectors.api
Interface IConnector

public interface IConnector

The Connector interface is implemented for each type of dynamic capacity provider. Dynamic capacity providers can be external cloud providers like Amazon EC2, Microsoft Azure, Rackspace Mosso. etc or internal virtualized pool of resources like VMware, Xen, Hyper-V, Solaris Zones etc. Each implementation must have a public no-arg constructor. Only that constructor will be used by the controller to create an instance of the connector implementation. Basic Concepts:

Compute Center - A Compute Center provides machines on demand.

Image Store - An Image Store stores Images that can be used to create new Machines.

Image - A virtual/cloud machine Image Machine - A virtual/cloud/physical machine

Method Detail

setControllerServices

void setControllerServices(IControllerServices controllerServices)
When the connector implementation is created it is passed a handle to the controller services. The implementor must maintain a reference to this object if it is needed when invoking other connector operations.

Parameters:
controllerServices - The controller services.

getAgentPort

int getAgentPort()
Retrieve the agent port for machine instances managed through this connector. Most likely it is the value returned from IControllerServices.getDefaultAgentPort().

Returns:
The agent port for the managed machine.

createMachine

IMachine createMachine(IComputeCenter computeCenter,
                       IImage image,
                       IMachineDescriptor machineDescriptor)
                       throws InvalidObjectException,
                              ConnectorException
Creates a new machine in the specified compute center, using the specified image. The type of machine and the hardware configuration etc, are specified in the machine descriptor. The implementation should try to not block the call until the machine is fully started. If possible, it should start the machine creation and return a Machine handle with the state set to MachineState.STARTING. The refreshMachineState(IMachine) method can then be called to check when machine startup is complete. If the Machine handle is created through the controller services interface then its' state will automatically be set to MachineState.STARTING.

Parameters:
computeCenter - The compute center where this machine should be created
image - The image used to create the machine
machineDescriptor - The descriptor of what kind of machine to be created
Returns:
The Machine handle. This handle should wrap an actual entity. This may be achieved by returning the machine created through the controller services interface.
Throws:
InvalidObjectException - If specified Compute Center or Image does not exist or is invalid
ConnectorException - If any error happens while starting the machine creation.

Throws:

terminateMachine

void terminateMachine(IMachine machine)
                      throws InvalidObjectException,
                             ConnectorException
Terminates the specified machine. The implementation should try to not block the call until the machine is fully terminated. If possible, it should start the machine termination and return immediately. Afterwards the Machine handle state will be set automatically to MachineState.STOPPING. The refreshMachineState(IMachine) method can then be called to check when machine termination is complete.

Throws:
InvalidObjectException - If Machine does not exist or is invalid
ConnectorException - If any error happens while starting the machine termination.

restartMachine

void restartMachine(IMachine machine)
                    throws InvalidObjectException,
                           ConnectorException
Restarts the specified machine. The implementation should try to not block the call until the machine is fully restarted. If possible it should begin the machine restart and return immediately. Afterwards the Machine handle state will be set automatically to MachineState.STARTING. The refreshMachineState(IMachine) method can then be called to check when machine restart is complete.

Throws:
InvalidObjectException - If Machine does not exist or is invalid
ConnectorException - If any error happens while starting the machine restart.

Throws:
InvalidObjectException - If the Image does not exist or is invalid

refreshImageState

void refreshImageState(IImage image)
                       throws InvalidObjectException,
                              ConnectorException
Refreshes the image state of the specified image. This callback is needed since the image save and image copy can take a considerable amount of time to complete. Instead of blocking on the image save and image copy operations, the connector implementation should return quickly. Afterwards, the controller will poll the image state through this operation to see when the image save or image copy is complete. When complete, it is the responsibility of the connector implementation to set the image state to ImageState.READY.

Parameters:
image - The image handle
Throws:
InvalidObjectException - If image does not exist or is invalid
ConnectorException - If any error happens while refreshing image state
